/Muslims\"}, {\"begin\": 822, \"end\": 828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9628488869168957, \"rank\": 0.03598142989088579, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8899247850192633, \"rank\": 0.06528312579200006, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They agreed that parts of the opening night festivities crossed a line, especially a shocking segment that included drag queens, partial nudity and a strange blue man who portrayed Dionysus-the ancient Greek god of drunkenness and orgies.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1105, \"end\": 1118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_art\", \"score\": 0.4487310834081306, \"rank\": 0.6536098347215556, \"text\": \"ancient Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_art\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek_art\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Within hours, video footage of the bizarre show disappeared from YouTube, and the Olympic Committee issued an apology.\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"score\": 0.9999999992583071, \"rank\": 7.417092167398294e-10, \"text\": \"YouTube\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Next, media commentators began arguing about whether the drag show segment was a mockery of Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"Last Supper\\\" painting or simply a depiction of ancient Greek gods doing lascivious things.\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1473,